OpenTelemetry

This product uses the OpenTelemetry Protocol (OTLP) specification and
imports packages from the OpenTelemetry project, which is licensed under
the Apache License 2.0.

  https://opentelemetry.io/
  https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-proto

---

HyperLogLog

The cardinality estimation feature uses the HyperLogLog algorithm as
described in:

  "HyperLogLog: the analysis of a near-optimal cardinality estimation algorithm"
  Philippe Flajolet, Éric Fusy, Olivier Gandouet, and Frédéric Meunier
  Conference on Analysis of Algorithms (AofA), 2007
  https://algo.inria.fr/flajolet/Publications/FlFuGaMe07.pdf

---

Development Process

This project uses OpenSpec for change management and specification-driven
development. Proposals, designs, and task tracking are maintained in the
openspec/ directory.

Portions of this codebase were developed with AI coding assistants
(GitHub Copilot, Claude). All AI-generated code has been reviewed,
tested, and approved by the project maintainers.
